messages.body: $UA Many stocks were shorted for near term gain taking advantage of over bought levels today across the board. Expect a SP pull back tomorrow across the board as "Turnaround Tuesday"  takes it share of profits on the down side for traders tomorrow. But look what is happening. We closed $1.15 higher today than where we were the beginning of last week. That is 9%+ higher week-over-week. For long term investors that is a solid gain. Not looking to get rich quick over night. Things like that rarely ever happen.

$UA So Susquehanna, you raised your PT on 10/28 from: $9 to $11 (the then current SP level). Not exactly a ballsy, Senior Analyst call don't you think? You might want to have the junior analyst/intern you had make that analysis re-evaluate that call to something a bit higher. At least more in line with the current SP trading level ($14) just 8 trading days later, don't you think?

$UA So we now have that bull pennant breakout today on top of Golden Cross of last week. We are now in recovery territory. Next, fill the gap between $16 and $17.85 to go. Then, who knows? It will all depend on the strength of the turnaround, retail comeback strength in general, and company plan execution. This is a long term deal. I really don't expect any new analyst upgrades until after Q4 ER.
$UA I was just at an Under Armor outlet store in PA. Place was packed. I think UA is starting their comeback before the holidays.
$GE regret selling 100 shares at 8.20 to buy $UA at 13.01 🤦🏻‍♂️

$UA Yesterday Morgan Stanley joined other in raising their PT. 
 
Morgan Stanley  Old PT $7   New PT $12   Rating Equal Weight 
 
Anyone else get the feeling that these institute holders of 75%+ of the stock are the ones actually holding the SP within a tight range so they can manipulate it for nickles, dimes and quarters on the millions of shares they own? They generate millions of $ each week doing it all the while reducing their actual SP down substantially. After all they own the market.  Just sayin'.

$UA Future moves? Last major unfilled gap between $16 and $17.85. Then back to the upper teens to $20 range again from last year. This will probably be a slow climb unless major manipulation occurs. Just sayin'.
selling $UA has been good protection during these tough times but going to use profits for $TOPS as underappreciated green play
